						<div class="postbody">How does QIX do this?<br /><br />It uses CHR-RAM, and doesn't seem to ever read from the PPU, so somehow it's using RAM...maybe extra RAM at $6000-7fff to keep track of what part of the screen has been written.<br /><br />Anyway, I did a modest move in Qix, and it split the CHR-RAM writes into 17 frames of writes.<br /><br />It also switches pattern tables for BG halfway down each frame.</div>

					
