						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Lucradan wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">And given there is only 1 bit in the rendering mask to indicate the tile page (typically background or sprite), how could you set it to a different page other than 1 or 0?</div><br />Mappers that support bankswitched CHR ROM also support bankswitched CHR RAM. On MMC3, for example, you'd write a window number (0 through 5) to $8000, then a 1K bank number (0 through 31) to $8001.</div><br />Just to point out, this requires emulator support for <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NES_2.0" class="postlink">the latest version of the iNES format</a> to specify the CHR-RAM size. Emulators that are up to date are okay with this, but if you want your game to run on older emulators, PowerPak, etc. this isn't really an option.</div>

